[
  [
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "(** * Pointwise Natural Transformations *)",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Require Import Category.Core Functor.Core NaturalTransformation.Core.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Require Import FunctorCategory.Core NaturalTransformation.Paths Functor.Composition.Core NaturalTransformation.Composition.Core.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Require Import Functor.Pointwise.Core.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Set Implicit Arguments.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Generalizable All Variables.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** Recall that a \"pointwise\" functor is a functor [A\u1d2e \u2192 C\u1d30] induced\n    by functors [D \u2192 B] and [A \u2192 C].  Given two functors [D \u2192 B] and a\n    natural transformation between them, there is an induced natural\n    transformation between the resulting functors between functor\n    categories, and similarly for two functors [A \u2192 C].  In this file,\n    we construct these natural transformations. They will be used to\n    construct the pointwise induced adjunction [F\u02e3 \u22a3 G\u02e3] of an\n    adjunction [F \u22a3 G] for all categories [X]. *)\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Open Scope morphism_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Open Scope category_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Open Scope functor_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Open Scope natural_transformation_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Section pointwise.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Context `{Funext}.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Variables C D C' D' : PreCategory.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Ltac t :=\n    path_natural_transformation; simpl;\n    rewrite <- ?composition_of;\n    try apply ap;\n    first [ apply commutes\n          | symmetry; apply commutes ].",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  (** ** [T\u02e3] for a natural transformation [T : F \u2192 G] and a functor [x : C \u2192 D] *)\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition pointwise_l\n             (F G : Functor C D)\n             (T : NaturalTransformation F G)\n             (F' : Functor C' D')\n  : NaturalTransformation (pointwise F F') (pointwise G F').",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
          "conclusion": "NaturalTransformation (pointwise F F') (pointwise G F')",
          "hypotheses": [
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "H"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "Funext"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "C"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "PreCategory"
            },
            {
